00:41:49,194 --> 00:41:50,729
No, that's- I'm fine.

492
00:41:50,825 --> 00:41:53,510
I just, uh-

493
00:41:53,606 --> 00:41:58,401
- I'm really tired.
- Oh. Well, let me show you the guest room.

494
00:41:58,497 --> 00:42:01,661
Um, it's right through here.
Uh, this is the bathroom.

495
00:42:01,757 --> 00:42:05,210
And I'll put out clean towels
and, uh, a washcloth.

496
00:42:05,401 --> 00:42:07,703
The bed's made up...

497
00:42:07,799 --> 00:42:10,388
and there are, um,
extra blankets in the closet.

498
00:42:12,210 --> 00:42:15,950
- Is my grandfather around?
- Oh. No.

499
00:42:16,046 --> 00:42:19,499
No, Ira passed away
over three years ago.

500
00:42:21,033 --> 00:42:23,527
So, you'll call me
if you need anything?

501
00:42:23,622 --> 00:42:25,636
Yeah.

502
00:42:41,268 --> 00:42:44,337
Hey, you said you didn't have children.

503
00:42:44,433 --> 00:42:47,022
I said I don't have children.

504
00:42:47,118 --> 00:42:50,091
I had a daughter.

505
00:42:50,283 --> 00:42:52,297
Her name was Caroline.
She died.

506
00:42:52,393 --> 00:42:54,119
What was she like?

507
00:42:56,420 --> 00:43:00,832
Well, she was-
she was exactly like that.

508
00:43:01,119 --> 00:43:03,325
Same eyes, same skin...

509
00:43:03,421 --> 00:43:05,435
same face- identical.

510
00:43:07,928 --> 00:43:10,901
But she had, um, health problems.

511
00:43:10,997 --> 00:43:14,258
- She had mental health problems.
- Tsk.

512
00:43:14,450 --> 00:43:16,559
Well, how'd she die?

513
00:43:21,163 --> 00:43:22,985
Car accident.

514
00:43:25,095 --> 00:43:27,108
A leave of absence? Why?

515
00:43:27,204 --> 00:43:29,698
I'm just-
I'm not happy at that firm.

516
00:43:29,890 --> 00:43:31,903
So instead you'll be walking dogs.

517
00:43:31,999 --> 00:43:35,164
And running errands, and-
I think it'll be fun.

518
00:43:36,890 --> 00:43:39,288
Are you okay?

519
00:43:39,384 --> 00:43:41,206
You're not having-

520
00:43:42,453 --> 00:43:45,042
- What?

521
00:43:45,138 --> 00:43:49,837
If you ever want to talk to someone,
Rose, I'll pay for it.

522
00:43:49,933 --> 00:43:53,097
No questions asked.
If you're ever feeling-

523
00:43:53,193 --> 00:43:55,687
Crazy?

524
00:43:55,879 --> 00:43:58,947
I'm not the one
you should be worried about.

525
00:43:59,043 --> 00:44:02,208
How is Maggie?

526
00:44:02,304 --> 00:44:04,797
- You haven't seen her?
- No, she's still with you, isn't she?

527
00:44:04,893 --> 00:44:09,688
Oh, yeah, she is. She's fine.

528
00:44:09,784 --> 00:44:12,182
- Thanks for the coffee.
- All right. See you soon?

529
00:44:12,373 --> 00:44:14,100
Yeah.

530
00:44:26,375 --> 00:44:29,252
The number
you have called is no longer in service.

531
00:44:29,348 --> 00:44:31,362
If you feel you have reached
this recording-

532
00:44:36,540 --> 00:44:38,362
Hmm.

533
00:44:45,267 --> 00:44:47,377
Well, good morning.

534
00:44:47,569 --> 00:44:49,295
Did you sleep well?

535
00:44:49,487 --> 00:44:51,213
Fine, thanks.

536
00:44:51,405 --> 00:44:54,761
I have English muffins here.
I can make you any kind of eggs you'd like.

537
00:44:54,857 --> 00:44:57,734
- I don't eat breakfast.
- Oh.

538
00:44:57,830 --> 00:44:59,652
I drink coffee.

539
00:45:01,187 --> 00:45:05,119
So, my goodness. This is a surprise.

540
00:45:05,214 --> 00:45:07,132
Such a lovely surprise.

541
00:45:08,571 --> 00:45:10,393
After all this time.

542
00:45:11,927 --> 00:45:14,709
- Yeah, what's up with that?
- I beg your pardon?

543
00:45:14,805 --> 00:45:19,408
Well, were you always out of the picture,
or just after Mom died?

544
00:45:19,504 --> 00:45:24,395
Oh, your grandfather and I were never out
of the- I mean, we were always there.

545
00:45:24,490 --> 00:45:26,313
We-

546
00:45:26,408 --> 00:45:29,861
And even after your mom died, I wrote.

547
00:45:30,149 --> 00:45:33,026
Birthday cards, every year.
And I never heard back.

548
00:45:33,217 --> 00:45:35,998
Yeah, I know. You wrote
for a while. I just found them.

549
00:45:36,094 --> 00:45:38,780
What do you mean,"just"?

550
00:45:38,780 --> 00:45:42,711
I guess they got waylaid.
Thanks for the money.

551
00:45:42,807 --> 00:45:45,972
You're telling me that your father
never gave you my cards?

552
00:45:46,068 --> 00:45:48,178
Mm-mmm.

553
00:45:48,178 --> 00:45:50,575
What must you have thought?

554
00:45:52,110 --> 00:45:54,891
I thought you both were dead.

555
00:45:59,302 --> 00:46:01,412
Does this place have a pool?

556
00:46:01,508 --> 00:46:04,289
- Oh! Sorry.
- Whoa.

557
00:46:04,385 --> 00:46:06,782
Whoa! Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa! Whoa!

558
00:46:06,878 --> 00:46:09,180
Come on.

559
00:46:09,180 --> 00:46:12,249
- Hey, check this out.

560
00:46:18,674 --> 00:46:20,784
Hey.

561
00:46:23,086 --> 00:46:25,387
Where'd she come from?

562
00:46:42,649 --> 00:46:44,567
Hi, sweetheart.

563
00:46:56,747 --> 00:46:58,569
Come on, come on.

564
00:47:18,708 --> 00:47:20,530
Come on. Keep playing.

565
00:47:23,599 --> 00:47:25,708
Rose! Rose Feller!

566
00:47:25,804 --> 00:47:27,818
Oh, Stein.

567
00:47:27,914 --> 00:47:29,928
How are you?

568
00:47:30,024 --> 00:47:33,380
Man, you look great.
Not sick at all.

569
00:47:33,476 --> 00:47:35,107
Why would I look sick?

570
00:47:35,203 --> 00:47:37,504
Oh.

571
00:47:37,600 --> 00:47:40,477
- That's one of the rumors.
- There are rumors?

572
00:47:44,601 --> 00:47:47,094
How 'bout that? Lunchtime.

573
00:47:47,190 --> 00:47:50,355
- Hey, how does, uh- How does Japanese sound?
- I'm not hungry, Stein.

574
00:47:50,451 --> 00:47:53,615
Oh, there's no such thing
as not hungry for sushi. Come on.

575
00:47:53,615 --> 00:47:56,205
We'll bill it to one of your old clients.

576
00:47:56,301 --> 00:47:58,123
Uh, thank you.
You eat everything?

577
00:47:58,219 --> 00:48:00,137
- What do you think?
- Okay.

578
00:48:00,328 --> 00:48:04,356
- Um, two orders of uni, one masago.
- Mm-hmm.

579
00:48:04,452 --> 00:48:06,178
- Uh, two tako.
- Okay.

580
00:48:06,274 --> 00:48:08,000
- Two hamachi.
- Mm-hmm.

581
00:48:08,096 --> 00:48:12,028
Then also that cod thing. It was a special
once, but it's not on the menu anymore.

582
00:48:12,028 --> 00:48:13,946
- You know what I'm talking about.
- Tara.

583
00:48:14,042 --> 00:48:15,864
- Yes!
- Okay. Thank you.

584
00:48:15,960 --> 00:48:18,837
- Okay, thank you.
- Thanks.

585
00:48:18,933 --> 00:48:21,139
- You just ordered for me.
- Yes.

586
00:48:21,235 --> 00:48:23,344
- What am I, 12?
- Uh, I'm an expert orderer.

587
00:48:23,536 --> 00:48:25,262
- It's a gift.
- Is it?

588
00:48:25,358 --> 00:48:27,948
Absolutely.

589
00:48:27,948 --> 00:48:31,017
What was the last
great restaurant you went to?

590
00:48:31,112 --> 00:48:34,661
- I took my sister to Le Bec Fin.
- Uh-huh.

591
00:48:34,757 --> 00:48:39,648
And you both got the... snapper,
right?

592
00:48:39,743 --> 00:48:41,757
Close. I got the snapper.

593
00:48:41,853 --> 00:48:45,497
- She got three rum and Cokes
and the sommelier's phone number.
- [ Laughs ] Okay.

594
00:48:45,593 --> 00:48:49,429
Well, I'll take you there,
and we'll get...

595
00:48:49,525 --> 00:48:53,553
the foie gras
with Roquefort-stuffed fig...

596
00:48:53,649 --> 00:48:56,142
Scottish wood pigeon with cabbage...

597
00:48:56,238 --> 00:48:58,636
and porcini cassoulet.

598
00:49:00,362 --> 00:49:02,280
And the chocolate mousse...

599
00:49:02,376 --> 00:49:04,773
with raspberries
and hazelnut macaroon.

600
00:49:04,869 --> 00:49:07,746
You'll want to eat with me
for the rest of your life.

601
00:49:12,062 --> 00:49:13,788
- Ah.
- Here you go.

602
00:49:13,788 --> 00:49:15,994
- Mmm.
- I know.

603
00:49:16,090 --> 00:49:17,912
- The special, tara.
- Thank you.

604
00:49:17,912 --> 00:49:19,830
Enjoy.

605
00:49:20,981 --> 00:49:23,953
So -
What are the other rumors?

606
00:49:24,049 --> 00:49:26,063
Ah. Um-

607
00:49:26,159 --> 00:49:29,132
Rumor one: mysterious illness.

608
00:49:29,228 --> 00:49:32,105
Rumor two: head-hunted
by Pepper and Hamilton.

609
00:49:34,982 --> 00:49:37,092
Here. Try some of this.

610
00:49:37,188 --> 00:49:40,257
- Rumor three?
- Um, soy?

611
00:49:40,352 --> 00:49:42,462
Oh, come on.
What's rumor three?

612
00:49:47,065 --> 00:49:49,751
Affair with a partner gone bad.

613
00:49:56,080 --> 00:49:57,902
Don't worry.

614
00:49:57,998 --> 00:50:00,108
Most people are betting on lupus.

615
00:50:07,109 --> 00:50:10,082
Here.
Wasabi makes everything better.

616
00:50:14,589 --> 00:50:17,562
- So, uh, what time Friday?
- Friday?

617
00:50:17,658 --> 00:50:19,480
Dinner.

618
00:50:19,576 --> 00:50:23,316
Oh, look, Simon, this was- this was
really nice, but, um, I don't think-

619
00:50:23,412 --> 00:50:25,234
7:00 it is.

620
00:50:28,111 --> 00:50:29,837
Thank you.

621
00:50:35,975 --> 00:50:38,276
Mmm. That smells good.
What is that?

622
00:50:38,468 --> 00:50:40,290
That's braised veal.

623
00:50:44,126 --> 00:50:46,044
- Shit.

624
00:50:46,140 --> 00:50:48,154
There's a paper towel on the counter.

625
00:50:54,483 --> 00:50:56,593
Out of curiosity...

626
00:50:56,689 --> 00:50:59,566
how long is this vacation of yours
going to last?

627
00:50:59,758 --> 00:51:02,827
How come you don't have
any pictures of my mom around?

628
00:51:02,923 --> 00:51:05,704
Don't you like thinking about her?

629
00:51:05,800 --> 00:51:08,677
I don't need to have a picture
to think about my daughter.

630
00:51:16,924 --> 00:51:20,185
You put out pictures,
people ask questions.

631
00:51:20,281 --> 00:51:23,158
They expect you to tell 'em everything,
and I don't do that.

632
00:51:23,253 --> 00:51:25,651
'Cause Mom was sick?

633
00:51:25,747 --> 00:51:27,953
Because she's gone.

634
00:51:30,158 --> 00:51:32,076
Is that why you pulled away from us?

635
00:51:32,172 --> 00:51:34,570
So that you didn't have to talk
about her with us either?

636
00:51:34,666 --> 00:51:37,543
I didn't pull away. I was pushed.

637
00:51:39,844 --> 00:51:41,666
No, listen.

638
00:51:41,762 --> 00:51:45,215
I'm not the one who didn't pass along
the letters. That was your father.

639
00:51:45,406 --> 00:51:47,229
I'm not the one
who didn't want a relationship.

640
00:51:47,324 --> 00:51:50,106
He said that?"I don't want you to have
a relationship with my daughters. "

641
00:51:50,201 --> 00:51:52,119
- Oh, yes.
- When?

642
00:51:52,215 --> 00:51:55,284
- At the funeral.
- Why? Why would he say that?

643
00:51:57,106 --> 00:52:01,038
Because he's irrational. Yeah.
He blamed me for everything.

644
00:52:01,134 --> 00:52:03,915
Every bad day, every bad episode.

645
00:52:04,011 --> 00:52:07,080
He did not want me near her.

646
00:52:07,176 --> 00:52:09,094
And after she was gone...

647
00:52:09,190 --> 00:52:12,546
he didn't want me near you
or your sister.

648
00:52:17,149 --> 00:52:18,972
I just wonder-

649
00:52:20,506 --> 00:52:25,589
If you had tried harder,
you know, or, like, tried again...

650
00:52:25,685 --> 00:52:28,849
after he'd gotten over the whole...

651
00:52:28,945 --> 00:52:31,822
shock and grief of it, you know?

652
00:52:35,275 --> 00:52:39,398
'Cause it would have been nice
having a grandmother.

653
00:52:39,398 --> 00:52:41,316
Nice and...

654
00:52:42,275 --> 00:52:44,385
maybe a little less lonely.

655
00:52:50,043 --> 00:52:53,016
She sounds like a manipulative
little nincompoop.

656
00:52:53,112 --> 00:52:56,660
- The girl lost her mother.
- So? You lost your daughter.

657
00:52:56,756 --> 00:52:58,674
- It's not the same.
- It's worse.

658
00:52:58,770 --> 00:53:01,935
A parent burying a child
goes against the law of nature.

659
00:53:02,127 --> 00:53:05,771
Well, so does a grandparent
abandoning her grandchildren.

660
00:53:05,867 --> 00:53:08,456
You said yourself
he didn't want you around.

661
00:53:08,552 --> 00:53:11,333
What were you supposed to do,
break down the door?

662
00:53:11,429 --> 00:53:13,251
Yes.

663
00:53:14,498 --> 00:53:16,320
Shoelace.

664
00:53:17,279 --> 00:53:20,923
For Caroline, yes.

665
00:53:21,019 --> 00:53:24,088
For Caroline.
She was gone, cookie.

666
00:53:24,184 --> 00:53:27,540
And you pushing your way into that house
wasn't gonna do a thing for her.

667
00:53:27,636 --> 00:53:30,034
- She wanted me there.
- You don't know that.

668
00:53:30,130 --> 00:53:33,390
- Yes, I do. I know.
- How?

669
00:53:35,020 --> 00:53:36,938
I just do.

670
00:53:37,034 --> 00:53:38,856
How?

671
00:53:41,254 --> 00:53:43,747
I've never told anybody this,
not even Ira.

672
00:53:43,843 --> 00:53:47,775
I'll take it to my grave,
probably tomorrow.

673
00:53:52,378 --> 00:53:54,296
It wasn't a car accident.

674
00:53:54,392 --> 00:53:57,653
I mean, eh- it- it was a car...

675
00:53:57,749 --> 00:54:02,256
and there was a crash, but-

676
00:54:03,886 --> 00:54:06,188
How do you know it was on purpose?

677
00:54:08,873 --> 00:54:10,695
She wrote a note.

678
00:54:13,572 --> 00:54:16,929
It came the day after the funeral.

679
00:54:17,121 --> 00:54:19,614
What'd it say?

680
00:54:19,710 --> 00:54:21,532
One line.

681
00:54:22,587 --> 00:54:25,272
"Please take care of my girls. "

682
00:54:25,368 --> 00:54:28,245
- And you didn't.
- [ Restrained Sobbing ] Mm-mmm.

683
00:54:28,341 --> 00:54:30,355
You didn't because you couldn't.

684
00:54:30,451 --> 00:54:32,561
Now you can, so you will.

685
00:54:32,657 --> 00:54:36,972
Ella, bubbeleh, you did the best
you could in a very bad situation.

686
00:54:37,068 --> 00:54:39,753
You got nothing to feel guilty about.

687
00:54:41,000 --> 00:54:44,452
And you tell that
to Miss Hotsy-Totsy Pants.

688
00:54:54,330 --> 00:54:57,303
So this is where all my boyfriends
have been coming from.

689
00:54:59,605 --> 00:55:03,345
They took a vote. I don't know who
I pissed off, but somehow... I lost.

690
00:55:03,441 --> 00:55:06,701
Or won. Either way, it's official.

691
00:55:06,797 --> 00:55:09,482
I am the captain of the softball team.

692
00:55:11,976 --> 00:55:13,798
Yeah.

693
00:55:15,332 --> 00:55:18,880
Look, I know this isn't my business,
but I can't not say anything.

694
00:55:18,976 --> 00:55:24,155
You have rights, legal options
for getting your job back.

695
00:55:24,251 --> 00:55:26,073
I don't want it back.

696
00:55:26,169 --> 00:55:28,758
You don't?

697
00:55:28,854 --> 00:55:30,964
I thought you loved it.

698
00:55:31,060 --> 00:55:34,129
You were always the first one there in the morning
and the last one to leave at night.

699
00:55:34,416 --> 00:55:37,773
I know. Not because I loved it.

700
00:55:37,869 --> 00:55:39,691
Then why?

701
00:55:40,746 --> 00:55:42,568
I don't know.

702
00:55:42,664 --> 00:55:46,404
Maybe... I was scared of what
would happen if I wasn't there.

703
00:55:46,500 --> 00:55:49,473
Oh, what? Like the place
would fall apart without you?

704
00:55:49,664 --> 00:55:53,117
- With law freaks like you there? Never.

705
00:55:53,213 --> 00:55:56,377
No, I wasn't worried about the office.

706
00:55:56,473 --> 00:55:59,638
I guess it was more... me...

707
00:55:59,734 --> 00:56:02,611
and what would happen to me
without those people to please...

708
00:56:02,707 --> 00:56:05,200
and those tasks to get done.

709
00:56:05,296 --> 00:56:08,940
Like... maybe... those were
the things holding me together.

710
00:56:10,667 --> 00:56:13,448
And without them, I'd...

711
00:56:13,544 --> 00:56:15,462
fall apart.

712
00:56:17,571 --> 00:56:19,969
But you didn't.

713
00:56:20,065 --> 00:56:21,887
I guess not.

714
00:56:24,189 --> 00:56:26,586
So what does hold you together?

715
00:56:34,929 --> 00:56:38,094
For me, it's the law, politics...

716
00:56:38,094 --> 00:56:40,108
the Sixers and good food.

717
00:56:40,204 --> 00:56:44,999
If you ever want to join me
for a game or a meal...

718
00:56:46,054 --> 00:56:47,972
I hope you'll give me a call.

719
00:57:03,891 --> 00:57:05,713
Ella?

720
00:57:39,374 --> 00:57:42,060
Oh. I was just looking for-

721
00:57:42,156 --> 00:57:43,978
For what?

722
00:57:47,814 --> 00:57:50,211
Sorry, I-

723
00:57:50,307 --> 00:57:53,568
Wrong dresser.
It's in the sock drawer.

724
00:57:53,664 --> 00:57:55,582
What is?

725
00:57:55,677 --> 00:57:59,513
My cash. That's what you were looking for,
right? That's what you want.

726
00:57:59,609 --> 00:58:02,582
No. God.

727
00:58:02,774 --> 00:58:06,131
Oh, well.

728
00:58:06,226 --> 00:58:08,912
I guess after being absent
for some 20-odd years or so...

729
00:58:09,008 --> 00:58:11,885
I can't expect you to want
to have a relationship with me.

730
00:58:11,981 --> 00:58:14,282
- How much?
- How much what?

731
00:58:14,474 --> 00:58:18,789
Money, Maggie. How much money
were you hoping to get from me?

732
00:58:21,283 --> 00:58:24,352
- I don't know.
- Yes, you do.

733
00:58:25,886 --> 00:58:28,667
I want to go to New York.

734
00:58:28,763 --> 00:58:33,270
Maybe... act.
I think I'd be good at it.

735
00:58:33,366 --> 00:58:36,435
Mmm, clearly.

736
00:58:36,531 --> 00:58:38,449
- How much do you need?
- Three grand.

737
00:58:38,545 --> 00:58:41,134
That you would not have found
in the sock drawer.

738
00:58:41,230 --> 00:58:43,148
How much do you have?

739
00:58:46,696 --> 00:58:48,519
Well...

740
00:58:48,614 --> 00:58:51,971
I won't give you $3,000,
