01:16:18,819 --> 01:16:20,353
Well, what can I get you?

990
01:16:20,832 --> 01:16:23,805
- I'll have a white wine, and he'll have the same.
- Oh, good.

991
01:16:24,573 --> 01:16:28,121
Why don't you just make yourself at home,
and I'll be right back.

992
01:16:29,080 --> 01:16:30,518
- Hey, Dad!
- Hello, sweetie.

993
01:16:30,998 --> 01:16:32,436
- Oh!
- Where's Maggie?

994
01:16:32,916 --> 01:16:35,505
- Oh, not here.
- Oh, thank God. We don't need
her drama tonight.

995
01:16:36,272 --> 01:16:39,245
- Why isn't she here? Is something wrong?
- No, we just had a fight.

996
01:16:40,108 --> 01:16:42,890
- About what?
- Can we talk about this later?

997
01:16:43,753 --> 01:16:46,246
Yes. Bad enough she monopolizes
the evening when she's here.

998
01:16:46,917 --> 01:16:48,931
Oh, let me see that ring.

999
01:16:51,425 --> 01:16:53,918
Oh, wow. Look at that.

1000
01:16:57,371 --> 01:17:00,248
Rose tells me you have a daughter
as well, Sydelle.

1001
01:17:01,015 --> 01:17:02,549
My Marcia? You'll meet her.

1002
01:17:03,029 --> 01:17:05,714
You'll love her. Everyone does.
My Marcia's a decorator.

1003
01:17:06,481 --> 01:17:07,632
Really?

1004
01:17:08,111 --> 01:17:10,509
She's an absolute genius in her work.

1005
01:17:11,180 --> 01:17:12,715
I'd like to say a few words.

1006
01:17:13,194 --> 01:17:16,071
Please. To Rose and Simon.

1007
01:17:16,934 --> 01:17:18,756
We're all blessed to be a part
of your happiness.

1008
01:17:19,332 --> 01:17:21,729
Your love bonds
notjust your two hearts...

1009
01:17:22,305 --> 01:17:24,510
but the hearts of two families.

1010
01:17:25,182 --> 01:17:26,716
- Mazel tov!
- Mazel tov!

1011
01:17:27,291 --> 01:17:29,018
- Mazel tov!
- Thanks, Dad.

1012
01:17:29,497 --> 01:17:31,415
- That went okay.
- Yeah.

1013
01:17:32,086 --> 01:17:33,621
Where's Maggie?

1014
01:17:34,100 --> 01:17:35,922
Uh, it's hard to say.
She moves around a lot.

1015
01:17:36,498 --> 01:17:38,895
Well, I want to meet her eventually,
you know? She's your sister.

1016
01:17:39,567 --> 01:17:41,772
- I want to know her.
- You will.

1017
01:17:42,444 --> 01:17:44,170
What was the fight about?

1018
01:17:44,745 --> 01:17:46,184
Mmm. Girl stuff.

1019
01:17:53,568 --> 01:17:55,102
Oh, shit.

1020
01:17:56,925 --> 01:17:58,363
Oh!

1021
01:17:58,843 --> 01:18:01,432
I should have used fresh vegetables
instead of frozen.

1022
01:18:02,199 --> 01:18:03,925
I don't think so. They were great.

1023
01:18:04,405 --> 01:18:06,419
- Really delicious. They were good.
- Really?

1024
01:18:07,090 --> 01:18:08,529
Yes.

1025
01:18:09,008 --> 01:18:11,981
- So, have you heard from Rose?
- No.

1026
01:18:12,844 --> 01:18:14,858
- So she hasn't gotten back to you.
- About what?

1027
01:18:15,433 --> 01:18:17,351
You were going
to invite her down, Maggie.

1028
01:18:18,023 --> 01:18:19,461
I don't know
where you got that idea.

1029
01:18:19,941 --> 01:18:22,338
Maggie,
I specifically asked you to.

1030
01:18:23,009 --> 01:18:25,982
So? Just because you specifically asked
doesn't mean I'm going to.

1031
01:18:26,750 --> 01:18:29,339
You shouldn't smoke.
You have a family history of lung cancer.

1032
01:18:30,106 --> 01:18:31,736
I have a family history
of car wrecks too.

1033
01:18:32,216 --> 01:18:34,038
Does that mean I shouldn't drive?

1034
01:18:34,613 --> 01:18:36,340
- That is not funny.
- It wasn't supposed to be.

1035
01:18:36,915 --> 01:18:38,641
All right, what is the problem
between you and Rose?

1036
01:18:39,217 --> 01:18:41,710
- Why don't you want her to visit?
- Why do you?

1037
01:18:42,477 --> 01:18:44,395
I mean,
am I not good enough for you?

1038
01:18:44,971 --> 01:18:46,985
This has nothing to do with you.

1039
01:18:47,656 --> 01:18:49,957
She's my daughter's daughter,
and I want to get to know her too.

1040
01:19:06,644 --> 01:19:08,179
What was Caroline like with you girls?

1041
01:19:08,754 --> 01:19:10,960
I mean, as a mom,
how do you remember her?

1042
01:19:11,631 --> 01:19:13,261
Why don't you ask Rose?

1043
01:19:13,741 --> 01:19:16,330
Maggie, please grow up.

1044
01:19:22,755 --> 01:19:24,290
She was special.

1045
01:19:24,673 --> 01:19:26,591
Different than the other moms.

1046
01:19:27,167 --> 01:19:28,701
She used to surprise us.

1047
01:19:31,770 --> 01:19:33,976
One time I opened up
my lunch box...

1048
01:19:35,414 --> 01:19:37,908
and there was a tiara inside.

1049
01:19:38,675 --> 01:19:40,593
A tiara. With your sandwich?

1050
01:19:41,264 --> 01:19:42,703
Instead of a sandwich.

1051
01:19:44,812 --> 01:19:46,730
What was she like as a daughter?

1052
01:19:48,457 --> 01:19:49,895
No tiaras.

1053
01:19:52,868 --> 01:19:55,170
But I loved her so much.

1054
01:19:59,102 --> 01:20:01,883
But loving her in the right way
was difficult, for me, anyway.

1055
01:20:02,650 --> 01:20:04,760
I didn't know there was
a right way and a wrong way.

1056
01:20:05,431 --> 01:20:06,965
Neither did I.

1057
01:20:08,404 --> 01:20:10,418
I had ideas-

1058
01:20:11,089 --> 01:20:14,062
I had unwelcomed ideas
about how to keep her safe.

1059
01:20:14,925 --> 01:20:16,651
Like?

1060
01:20:17,035 --> 01:20:19,624
Like, I thought she should have been
on her medication all the time.

1061
01:20:20,391 --> 01:20:22,118
I thought that her relationship
with your father...

1062
01:20:22,693 --> 01:20:24,515
was far too passionate
for her to handle.

1063
01:20:25,091 --> 01:20:26,529
And as far as children
were concerned...

1064
01:20:27,009 --> 01:20:29,406
she was in no condition,
no condition at all.

1065
01:20:30,173 --> 01:20:32,379
So you wish she never had me.

1066
01:20:35,544 --> 01:20:37,078
You know what I wish, Maggie?

1067
01:20:39,380 --> 01:20:41,394
I wish I'd kept my big mouth
shut long enough...

1068
01:20:42,065 --> 01:20:43,887
to hear what she wanted
out of life.

1069
01:20:53,093 --> 01:20:55,587
There she is! There's the bride!

1070
01:20:57,888 --> 01:20:59,135
Be strong.

1071
01:21:00,957 --> 01:21:04,410
Stay right here.
I'll get your corsage.

1072
01:21:05,369 --> 01:21:07,478
Corsage? What is this, a prom?

1073
01:21:08,150 --> 01:21:09,780
- Ladies?
- Ah, thank you.

1074
01:21:12,369 --> 01:21:15,055
- Who are these people?
- I have no idea.

1075
01:21:15,822 --> 01:21:18,507
- Except for my Marcia.
- Hello!

1076
01:21:19,274 --> 01:21:21,480
Hey, you're not sticking around...

1077
01:21:22,151 --> 01:21:25,028
to watch me ooh and ahh
over a Mixmaster Deluxe?

1078
01:21:25,891 --> 01:21:27,809
It's good of you
to let Sydelle do this.

1079
01:21:28,481 --> 01:21:31,166
- Oh, like gale force winds could stop her.
- Go easy on her.

1080
01:21:31,933 --> 01:21:34,426
- Marcia's giving her a very hard time these days.
- Oh, what's she doing?

1081
01:21:35,002 --> 01:21:37,016
Decorating in last year's colors?

1082
01:21:37,687 --> 01:21:39,605
She joined Jews forJesus.

1083
01:21:44,592 --> 01:21:46,318
Yoo-hoo! Ladies, it's time...

1084
01:21:46,798 --> 01:21:49,771
for the entertainment portion
of our soiree.

1085
01:21:50,634 --> 01:21:53,223
Uh, everyone get where you can see.
Anita, Jackie, come on.

1086
01:21:53,990 --> 01:21:56,196
Scoot.
Here we go.

1087
01:21:56,771 --> 01:21:58,306
Aw!

1088
01:21:58,689 --> 01:22:00,895
We, who know Rose,
are so thrilled...

1089
01:22:01,566 --> 01:22:04,251
that this day has finally arrived.

1090
01:22:05,019 --> 01:22:07,704
- Aw.
- There was a time we had our doubts.

1091
01:22:10,293 --> 01:22:11,828
Oh, my goodness.

1092
01:22:12,307 --> 01:22:15,376
All that time spent with her nose
buried in her book.

1093
01:22:16,335 --> 01:22:17,965
- Oh, bookworm.

1094
01:22:18,445 --> 01:22:22,760
Of course, there were romances,
but for some reason or other, nothing stuck.

1095
01:22:24,007 --> 01:22:26,500
- Oh!
- A little heavy.

1096
01:22:27,172 --> 01:22:31,295
- Oh. One thing Rose always
had was a great appetite.

1097
01:22:32,446 --> 01:22:33,981
For life!

1098
01:22:42,803 --> 01:22:44,242
Oh, God!

1099
01:22:44,721 --> 01:22:47,023
Why would anyone want to marry me?
I'm disgusting!

1100
01:22:47,694 --> 01:22:50,475
The only disgusting person here
is your stepmother. She's hideous.

1101
01:22:51,339 --> 01:22:53,832
So why is she giving me this party?
She hates me.

1102
01:22:54,503 --> 01:22:56,421
Someone else should do it-
someone who I-loves me...

1103
01:22:57,093 --> 01:22:58,819
someone who can look at me
and say...

1104
01:22:59,298 --> 01:23:01,792
"All of this is nothing more
than the happiness you deserve. "

1105
01:23:02,559 --> 01:23:04,093
Young lady.

1106
01:23:04,573 --> 01:23:06,587
Rose Feller,
don't you dare walk out on-

1107
01:23:07,258 --> 01:23:09,464
- I am talking to my friend!

1108
01:23:10,135 --> 01:23:12,628
She's crazy. She's crazy!
She's sick in the head!

1109
01:23:22,506 --> 01:23:25,575
Hands down,
best shower I've ever been to.

1110
01:23:33,151 --> 01:23:35,069
Engagement should be
a happy time, Rosie.

1111
01:23:35,549 --> 01:23:38,138
So should childhood and graduation.

1112
01:23:38,905 --> 01:23:40,439
And happy hour.

1113
01:23:40,823 --> 01:23:43,700
Did you know more suicides happen during
happy hour than any other time of day?

1114
01:23:44,563 --> 01:23:46,577
- Is that true?
- I wouldn't doubt it.

1115
01:23:50,029 --> 01:23:51,564
I love you, you know.

1116
01:24:07,100 --> 01:24:09,593
- Who's Rose?
- There's this thing called privacy, Dora.

1117
01:24:14,772 --> 01:24:18,032
This from a girl who puts a postage stamp
on her bottom and calls it a swimsuit.

1118
01:25:31,780 --> 01:25:34,081
The number
you have called is no longer in service.

1119
01:25:34,753 --> 01:25:36,862
If you feel you have reached
this recording in error-

1120
01:25:45,685 --> 01:25:47,699
Hmm.

1121
01:25:54,604 --> 01:25:56,042
Hey.

1122
01:25:59,207 --> 01:26:00,837
Are you dead?

1123
01:26:01,413 --> 01:26:03,235
What were you thinking,
going to the mall?

1124
01:26:03,810 --> 01:26:05,728
The mall is for young people,
people with teeth.

1125
01:26:06,304 --> 01:26:08,605
Well, my son's finally getting married,
and the girl's a ninny.

1126
01:26:09,181 --> 01:26:12,346
"Shut up, Ma," he says.
"Just show up in something nice. "

1127
01:26:13,305 --> 01:26:14,839
- You know what I saw today?
- What?

1128
01:26:15,318 --> 01:26:19,250
Pants with "Juicy" written across the heinie.
I'm gonna wear that?

1129
01:26:20,305 --> 01:26:22,223
Just wear something
you're comfortable in.

1130
01:26:22,895 --> 01:26:25,292
I haven't been comfortable
since the Dodgers left Brooklyn.

1131
01:26:27,498 --> 01:26:29,224
What's your favorite thing
you ever wore?

1132
01:26:29,799 --> 01:26:31,909
- Ever?
- Yeah. In your whole life.

1133
01:26:32,580 --> 01:26:35,553
My going-away suit
from my wedding.

1134
01:26:36,416 --> 01:26:38,622
Black and white checks,
very fitted.

1135
01:26:39,294 --> 01:26:41,307
I felt likeJackie Kennedy in that suit.

1136
01:26:47,541 --> 01:26:50,130
Give me your credit card.
Give it to me.

1137
01:26:55,405 --> 01:26:56,939
Can I get you a size?

1138
01:27:00,967 --> 01:27:03,652
No, I'm going to
the women's suit department.

1139
01:27:15,544 --> 01:27:16,982
So?

1140
01:27:18,900 --> 01:27:22,257
-Jackie Kennedy?
- Better. Jackie Onassis.

1141
01:27:26,381 --> 01:27:27,915
That looks so good on you.

1142
01:27:28,490 --> 01:27:30,984
Oh, Maggie, you're so sweet.
Good job!

1143
01:27:38,272 --> 01:27:39,615
You ready?

1144
01:27:40,094 --> 01:27:41,916
I don't know what to wear
to a Main Line wedding.

1145
01:27:42,492 --> 01:27:44,218
It doesn't matter.
Wear whatever you want.

1146
01:27:44,793 --> 01:27:46,999
- Believe me, when the bride's
name is Lopey, it matters.
- Look, th-that looks great.

1147
01:27:47,670 --> 01:27:49,109
- Come on.
- Really?

1148
01:27:49,588 --> 01:27:52,178
- Yeah. Come on. We gotta go.
- Okay.

1149
01:27:52,849 --> 01:27:54,767
I can't believe you have
a friend named Lopey.

1150
01:27:55,342 --> 01:27:57,260
- Come on, come on, come on.
- I'm sorry. Wait.

1151
01:28:02,631 --> 01:28:05,124
Are you okay? 'Cause if there's gonna be
any stabbing, I need a little heads up.

1152
01:28:05,796 --> 01:28:08,001
I'm fine.

1153
01:28:12,604 --> 01:28:14,331
Oh, my God.

1154
01:28:14,714 --> 01:28:17,016
Oh, shit. MyJimmy Choos!

1155
01:28:20,277 --> 01:28:22,290
Chewing gum?

1156
01:28:22,866 --> 01:28:24,400
Oh, that bitch. That bitch!

1157
01:28:24,976 --> 01:28:27,277
- No one will notice.
- Right. No one's gonna notice that.

1158
01:28:27,949 --> 01:28:31,305
"Hi. Hi. Hi! Hi. I can talk, 'cause I
have a mouth. " My heel has a mouth!

1159
01:28:32,264 --> 01:28:33,511
No one will notice.

1160
01:28:33,990 --> 01:28:36,771
Oh, my God!
What happened to your heel?

1161
01:28:42,429 --> 01:28:45,690
Uh, best wishes, Lopey, Jordan.

1162
01:28:46,553 --> 01:28:48,088
Thanks, Simon.

1163
01:28:49,910 --> 01:28:52,595
"Let the wind die down.

1164
01:28:53,362 --> 01:28:56,719
"Let the... shed go black inside.

1165
01:28:57,678 --> 01:29:00,075
"Let evening come.

1166
01:29:00,842 --> 01:29:04,007
"To the bottle in the ditch...

1167
01:29:04,870 --> 01:29:07,555
"to the scoop... in the oats...

1168
01:29:09,665 --> 01:29:13,118
"to... air in the lung...

1169
01:29:16,186 --> 01:29:18,488
let evening come. "

1170
01:29:26,735 --> 01:29:28,845
- [Jim ] Can I take that for you?

1171
01:29:29,517 --> 01:29:32,681
I hear you're getting married.
Congratulations.

1172
01:29:35,942 --> 01:29:37,668
Congratulations are for the groom.

1173
01:29:38,243 --> 01:29:39,778
You say "best wishes" to the bride.

1174
01:29:40,257 --> 01:29:42,367
I guess my manners aren't
what they should be.

1175
01:29:43,038 --> 01:29:45,628
Gee, really?

1176
01:29:46,395 --> 01:29:48,313
Rose, I am really sorry.

1177
01:29:48,888 --> 01:29:51,382
I've felt horrible about myself
for two solid months.

1178
01:29:52,053 --> 01:29:53,779
I've felt horrible
about myself my whole life...

1179
01:29:54,259 --> 01:29:55,793
so you'll get no sympathy from me.

1180
01:30:01,835 --> 01:30:05,000
You know what they called me
growing up?

1181
01:30:05,959 --> 01:30:08,356
Fudgie the Whale.

1182
01:30:09,027 --> 01:30:10,945
I'm still shocked
when a woman wants me...

1183
01:30:11,425 --> 01:30:14,781
and sometimes I do really stupid things
because I can't believe I can.

1184
01:30:15,740 --> 01:30:18,042
- That thing with your sister-
- Was inexcusable.

1185
01:30:19,864 --> 01:30:22,166
No matter what you weighed
in high school.

1186
01:30:22,837 --> 01:30:24,755
You ruined everything.

1187
01:30:26,673 --> 01:30:28,591
I know.

1188
01:30:29,167 --> 01:30:31,085
What we had... was really special.

1189
01:30:34,921 --> 01:30:36,455
Oh, please! What we-

1190
01:30:40,387 --> 01:30:45,470
Because of you,
I have no idea where my sister is.

1191
01:30:46,812 --> 01:30:47,579
I can't reach her.
Her phone's cut off.

1192
01:30:47,867 --> 01:30:50,265
She doesn't even know I'm engaged.
My own sister.

1193
01:30:51,032 --> 01:30:53,429
My best friend.

1194
01:30:54,101 --> 01:30:56,882
And the worst part is,
I can't talk to anyone about it.

1195
01:30:57,745 --> 01:31:00,046
If I tell my father, he'll get
all panicked and mad at me...

1196
01:31:00,718 --> 01:31:02,540
for not taking better care of her.

1197
01:31:03,115 --> 01:31:06,664
And if I tell Simon-
I can't tell Simon.

1198
01:31:07,718 --> 01:31:09,349
Why not?

1199
01:31:09,732 --> 01:31:11,363
Because...

1200
01:31:13,472 --> 01:31:15,007
he'll hate her.

1201
01:31:16,829 --> 01:31:18,843
And that, I couldn't bear.

1202
01:31:30,926 --> 01:31:32,269
Hi, Jim.

1203
01:31:34,283 --> 01:31:37,256
Here I am, trying to be patient,
trying to be understanding...

1204
01:31:38,023 --> 01:31:39,557
while you lose your freaking mind.

1205
01:31:40,037 --> 01:31:42,818
- I'm not losing my mind.
- Ping-ponging between
comatose and homicidal.

1206
01:31:43,681 --> 01:31:46,942
God, every day I wake up thinking,
"Maybe today's the day she'll come back.

1207
01:31:47,709 --> 01:31:50,010
- I'm right here.
- "Maybe today she'll look at me like she used to.

1208
01:31:50,778 --> 01:31:53,846
She'll- She'll look at me in the eye,
tell me what she's thinking. "

1209
01:31:54,710 --> 01:31:56,148
- Simon?
- But no, no, no.

1210
01:31:56,628 --> 01:31:58,450
Today's the day
you look him in the eye...

1211
01:31:59,025 --> 01:32:00,560
tell him what you're thinking.

1212
01:32:01,039 --> 01:32:04,779
The guy who treated you
like a- like a disposable washrag.

1213
01:32:29,617 --> 01:32:32,111
This has nothing to do with him.

1214
01:32:32,878 --> 01:32:34,508
This is about you and me-

1215
01:32:34,988 --> 01:32:39,207
you not talking to me, you not
telling me what's going on inside you.

1216
01:32:41,988 --> 01:32:43,619
Tell me.

1217
01:32:50,715 --> 01:32:52,633
I won't marry you like this.

